The escape velocity from a black hole exceeds the speed of light. The formula for escape velocity is 
V=2MG/R{\displaystyle V={\sqrt {2MG/R}}} 
for an object at radius R from a spherical mass M, with G being the gravitational constant. When the velocity is the speed of light, c, the radius, Rs=2MG/c2,{\displaystyle R_{\text{s}}=2MG/c^{2},} is called the Schwarzschild radius.: 27
